==The EMEP/EEA aviation methodology==
The [[http://www.eea.europa.eu/publications/emep-eea-emission-inventory-guidebook-2009|guidebook]] provides detailed fuel consumption data for over 140 specific jet, turboprop and military aircraft types, and represents the foremost methodology for calculation aviation-associated greenhouse gas emissions. 

Aircraft fuel consumption dynamics are differentiated by into associated with landing and take off (LTO) phases (taxiing, take off, climb out, landing) and cruising at altitude. This fuel consumption is converted into CO,,2,, emissions by using a CO,,2,, emissions factor of 3.15 (kg CO,,2,, per kg fuel). This value corresponds to the CO,,2,, emissions factor for 'jet fuel' specified by the IPCC (1999).

